1945;;Swingin' on a Rainbow;;American;;William Beaudine;;Jane Frazee;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swingin%27_on_a_Rainbow;;At a radio station run by Thomas Marsden, a songwriter, Jimmy Rhodes, skips town without fulfilling a contractual obligation, so amateur songstress Lynn Bird is hired to replace him, Marsden mistakenly believing her to be Rhodes's partner.Bird composes and writes a few songs, with help from Marsden's assistant, Chester Willoughby, and her success helps save the station.